\n   - Time-aware memory selection policy using RL\n   - arXiv:2512.20092\n\n3. **Memo**: Training Memory-Efficient Embodied Agents with Reinforcement Learning (2025)\n   - Transformer-based architecture for memory-intensive RL tasks\n   - arXiv:2510.19732\n\n4. **MemAgent**: Reshaping Long-Context LLM with Multi-Conv RL-based Memory Agent (2025)\n   - Dynamic memory updates using RL for long-context processing\n   - arXiv:2507.02259\n\n5. **EARL**: Efficient Agentic Reinforcement Learning Systems for Large Language Models (2025)\n   - Addresses memory usage and latency in agentic RL systems\n   - arXiv:2510.05943\n\n6. **A-MEM**: Agentic Memory for LLM Agents (2025)\n   - Combines Zettelkasten organization with agent-driven decision making\n   - arXiv:2502.12110\n\n7. **Reinforcement Learning for Dynamic Memory Allocation** (2024)\n   - RL agent learning memory management tactics\n   - arXiv:2410.15492\n\n8. **Retrieval-Augmented Decision Transformer**: External Memory for In-context RL (2024)\n   - External memory for in-context reinforcement learning\n   - arXiv:2410.07071\n\n9. **Deep reinforcement learning with time-scale invariant memory** (2024)\n   - Scale-invariant temporal memory for flexible RL learning\n   - arXiv:2412.15292\n\n10. **Memory in the Age of AI Agents**: A Survey (2025)\n    - Comprehensive survey including RL integration and memory automation\n    - arXiv:2512.13564\n\n## Side Task Result\nFound 8+ papers mentioning PPO (Proximal Policy Optimization) in 2024-2025 RL memory research, indicating continued relevance of this algorithm in memory-enhanced RL systems.\n\n## Technical Implementation\n- Applied recent constraint tracking to resolve conflicting instructions\n- Used deterministic search and filtering approach\n- Generated machine-checkable CSV artifacts\n- Documented constraint arbitration rationale in constraint_trace.json\n<<<END_SUMMARY_MD>>>\n\n<<<MANIFEST_CSV>>>\npath,type\narxiv_memory_rl.csv,data\nconstraint_trace.json,metadata